  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <div class="well">
      <pubtit>Ubiquitous selfish toxin-antidote elements in Caenorhabditis species</pubtit>
      <p><img src="/images/pubpic/tropics.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>We discovered five toxin-antidote (TAs) seflish elements in <em>C. tropicalis</em> and one in <em>C. briggsae</em>. Our work suggests they are common in nematodes, and in animals in general.</p>
      <p><em>E. Ben-David*, P. Pliota*, S. A. Widen, A. Koreshova, T. Lemus-Vergara, P. Verpukhovskiy, S. Mandali, C. Braendle, A. Burga, L. Kruglyak</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://doi.org/10.1101/2020.08.06.240564">bioRxiv (2020)</a></strong></p>
      <p class="text-danger"><strong> </strong></p>
      <p> </p>
    </div>
