</div>

<div class="row">

  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <div class="well">
      <pubtit>Fast genetic mapping of complex traits in C. elegans using millions of individuals in bulk</pubtit>
      <p><img src="/images/pubpic/xqtl.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>We developed a method to quickly map genetic loci affecting complex traits in extremely large populations in <em>C. elegans</em>.</p>
      <p><em>A. Burga*, E. Ben-David*, T. Lemus Vergara, J. Boocock, L. Kruglyak</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-019-10636-9">Nat Commun. 10, 2680 (2019)</a></strong></p>
      <p class="text-danger"><strong> </strong></p>
      <p> </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 clearfix">
    <div class="well">
      <pubtit>A maternal-effect selfish genetic element in Caenorhabditis elegans</pubtit>
      <p><img src="/images/pubpic/pha1.png" class="img-responsive" width="33%" style="float: left" /></p>
      <p>We discovered that <em>pha-1</em>, a gene thought to be essential for nematode worm development is, in fact, part of a toxin-antidote selfish genetic element.</p>
      <p><em>E. Ben-David*, A. Burga*, L. Kruglyak</em></p>
      <p><strong><a href="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aan0621">Science. 356, Issue 6342 (2017)</a></strong></p>
      <p class="text-danger"><strong> </strong></p>
      <p> covered in <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0960982217308898">current biology</a>, <a href="https://arstechnica.com/science/2017/05/worm-moms-pumps-eggs-full-of-toxin-demand-they-inherit-an-antidote/">ars technica</a>, <a href="https://www.sciencenews.org/article/selfish-genes-hide-decades-plain-sight-worm-geneticists">science news</a>, <a href="https://phys.org/news/2017-05-worms-reveals-selfish-genes-encode.html">phys.org</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

